<!doctype qwertz system>

<manpage title="PtlInit" sectnum="3" date='"04 Jan 2001"'
    footer='"Portals 3.0"' main='"Portals 3.0 Library"'>

<sect1> NAME
    <p>
    <bf/PtlInit/ &mdash Initialize the Portals 3.0 Library 
    </p>

<sect1> SYNOPSIS
    <p>
     #include "p30.h"

     int PtlInit(void)
    </p>

<sect1> DESCRIPTION
    <p>
    <bf /PtlInit/ should be called by all processes in an application before
    calling any of the functions defined by the Portal API.  This function
    should be called once and only once during initialization by each process
    in a parallel job.
    </p>

<sect1> RETURN VALUES
    <p>
    <descrip>
     <tag /PTL_OK/
     on success
     <tag /PTL_FAIL/
     indicates an error during initialization
    </descrip>
    </p>

<sect1> SEE ALSO
    <p>
    <bf /PtlFini(3)/<newline>
    <bf /Portals 3.0 Message Passing Interface document/
    </p>

</manpage>
